title: SAN JACINTO: Parent, student conference set
text:
BY CRAIG SHULTZ / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 22, 2015 1:20 p.m. SAN JACINTO: Parent, student conference set Print Photo Share Pin It 1 of 2 More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article » San Jacinto Unified School District and Mt. San Jacinto College will hosting the eighth annual “Into the Future” parent and student conference, designed to foster a college-bound culture in the San Jacinto Valley.
The free event will be from 8:30 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Saturday at the MSJC San Jacinto campus, 1499 N. State St.
Participants can attend two sessions from a choice of 10 workshops, with several held in Spanish. A free light breakfast and lunch will be provided and free transportation will be provided from San Jacinto school sites to the MSJC campus beginning at 8 a.m. Free childcare also is available at the MSJC campus.
Contact the writer: 951-368-9086 or cshultz@pe.com
